There are many movies that attempt to capture the pure joy wtihin humanity. People in these movies go on exotic vacations or trips in search of happinest. Some spend extra uninterupted time from their family. Happiness, in these movies, is always a journey. The character or characters often realize they are not happy at their job, in their location, with something in their family and decide to change. Therefore, I think happiness has more in the journey of life rather than a goal achieved. 

Happiness tends to start when the person realizes that this is not what they were hoping would happen in life.

Disney claims to be the happiest place on earth. Yet for introverts like myself, it tends to be very anxiety inducing and overwhelming. Some food brands claim that eating their product will make you happy. What about the people who are allergic to that product? Can they not find happiness because they cannot consume that food? Happiness, is a subjective term and therefore I believe happiness is something that can be found anywhere at any moment if you are looking for it. \n\nHappiness is subjective. All subjective means is that people will have different responses for what brings them happiness. While Disney world gives me anxiety, I have seen the joy on many other faces as they visit! I am always super happy when I get to eat a cannoli. I believe cannolis are made with joy and served with joy. However, if someone has never eaten a cannoli does that mean they cannot experience happiness? Absolutely not. They had opportunities to find happiness in many other ways.
